    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-09-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="501"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                <head>No. 501.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Señor <persName
                            type="to">Navarro</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-09-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 11, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 28th ultimo, representing that certain bandits, headed by one
                    Robert Martin, have a haunt in the Sierra de la Hacha, in American territory, on
                    the Texas frontier, whence they make raids into Mexico for the purpose of
                    stealing cattle and bringing them on this side of the line.</p>
                <p>In reply, I have to express my regret that Mexican citizens in that quarter
                    should suffer from such depredations, and to state whatever measures may be in
                    the power of this government towards preventing them shall at once be taken.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
